 Egyptian court has sentenced a popular Armenian belly dancer to six months in prison for ` insulting the Egyptian flag after she wore a tight dress in its red , white and black color scheme .
The court in Agouza said Sofinar Gourian was fined £ 15,000 after being found guilty in a case raised by a private complainant .
She is expected to avoid jail time after paying £ 10,000 bail and launching an appeal against the six month prison sentence .